        >>[ ] description #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3b5faede09e7
    >[ ] migrate existing plan .ics files from VEVENT\+RRULE to VTODO\+RRULE $One-time conversion command, not a permanent dual-format read path. Run once after plan_to_event/parse_ics_file switch to VTODO; old VEVENT plan format is retired after conversion. See caldav-integration/README.md design notes 2026-07-12.$ #019f59c4-8c0b-7aa1-88b8-8ec35dee0e2d
    >[ ] extract calendar sync into its own crate $Once VTODO bidirectional behavior settles, consider lifting the plans-vdir projection plus its local merge-base store from clearhead-core into a boundary-named crate such as clearhead-vdir. It may depend on core for parsing, formatting, and PendingBatch durability. Do not introduce CalDAV server, account, remote, or pair concepts.$ #019f5f76-f52a-7251-bd29-28117bf16f47
    >[ ] make Action UUID the VTODO identity $For standalone actions use one identity end-to-end: Action.id == VTODO UID == vdir filename. Remove redundant sidecar mirror-ID linkage and audit source_vevent/external_schedule_id usage so recurrence-series metadata is kept only where it is semantically real.$ !1 #019f7455-fde8-7112-a9cc-2955902ae771
